{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idee2a506f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s361a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"361a"},"text":"§ 361a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional declaration of purpose; definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It is the policy of Congress to continue the agricultural research at State agricultural experiment stations which has been encouraged and supported by the Hatch Act of 1887 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s361a"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 361a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], the Adams Act of 1906, the Purnell Act of 1925, the Bankhead-Jones Act of 1935, and title I, section 9, of that Act as added by the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-08-14"},"text":"August 14, 1946","children":[],"tail":", and Acts amendatory and supplementary thereto, and to promote the efficiency of such research by a codification and simplification of such laws. As used in this Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s361a"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 361a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], the terms “State” or “States” are defined to include the several States (including the District of Columbia), Puerto Rico, Guam and the Virgin Islands. As used in this Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s361a"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 361a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], the term “State agricultural experiment station” means a department which shall have been established, under direction of the college or university or agricultural departments of the college or university in each State in accordance with an Act approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1862-07-02"},"text":"July 2, 1862","children":[],"tail":", ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/12/503"},"text":"12 Stat. 503","children":[],"tail":"), entitled “An Act donating public lands to the several States and Territo­ries which may provide colleges for the benefit of agriculture and the mechanic arts” ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s301"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 301","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]; or such other substantially equivalent arrangements as any State shall determine."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idee2a5070-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1887-03-02/ch314/s1"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1887, ch. 314, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/24/440"},"text":"24 Stat. 440","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-08-11/ch790/s1"},"text":"Aug. 11, 1955, ch. 790, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/671"},"text":"69 Stat. 671","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/318/tV/s506/k"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–318, title V, § 506(k)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-06-23"},"text":"June 23, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/351"},"text":"86 Stat. 351","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/471/tII/s208/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–471, title II, § 208(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-26"},"text":"Oct. 26, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1429"},"text":"88 Stat. 1429","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/185/tII/s203/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–185, title II, § 203(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-06-23"},"text":"June 23, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/534"},"text":"112 Stat. 534","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idee2a5071-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idee2a5072-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idee2a5073-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Hatch Act of 1887, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1887-03-02/ch314"},"text":"act Mar. 2, 1887, ch. 314","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/24/440"},"text":"24 Stat. 440","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to sections 361a to 361i of this title. For complete classification of this act to the Code, see Short Title note set out below, and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Adams Act of 1906, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1906-03-16/ch951"},"text":"act Mar. 16, 1906, ch. 951","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/34/63"},"text":"34 Stat. 63","children":[],"tail":", which was classified to sections 361, 366, 369, 371, 373 to 376, 380, and 382 of this title, and was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-08-11/ch790/s2"},"text":"act Aug. 11, 1955, ch. 790, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/674"},"text":"69 Stat. 674","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code prior to repeal, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Purnell Act of 1925, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1925-02-24/ch308"},"text":"act Feb. 24, 1925, ch. 308","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/970"},"text":"43 Stat. 970","children":[],"tail":", which was classified to sections 361, 366, 370, 371, 373 to 376, 380, and 382 of this title, and was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-08-11/ch790/s2"},"text":"act Aug. 11, 1955, ch. 790, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/674"},"text":"69 Stat. 674","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code prior to repeal, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Bankhead-Jones Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-06-29/ch338"},"text":"act June 29, 1935, ch. 338","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/436"},"text":"49 Stat. 436","children":[],"tail":", also popularly known as the Agricultural Research Act. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title of 1935 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s3101"},"text":"section 3101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Title I, section 9, of that Act, referred to in text, was classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s427h"},"text":"section 427h of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to repeal."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Act approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1862-07-02"},"text":"July 2, 1862","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/12/503"},"text":"12 Stat. 503","children":[],"tail":"), referred to in text, is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1862-07-02/ch130"},"text":"act July 2, 1862, ch. 130","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/12/503"},"text":"12 Stat. 503","children":[],"tail":", popularly known as the “Morrill Act” and also as the “First Morrill Act”, which is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 301 et seq.) of chapter 13 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s301"},"text":"section 301 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idee2a5074-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/471/s208"},"text":"Section 208 of Pub. L. 93–471","children":[],"tail":", cited as a credit to this section, was renumbered section “209” by D.C. Law 1–36, § 4, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":", 22 DCR 2911."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s362"},"text":"section 362 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idee2a5075-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/185"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–185","children":[],"tail":" struck out “Alaska, Hawaii,” before “Puerto Rico” in second sentence."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1974—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/471"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–471","children":[],"tail":" defined “State” to include the District of Columbia."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1972—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/318"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–318","children":[],"tail":" defined “State” to include Guam and the Virgin Islands."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1955—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-08-11"},"text":"Aug. 11, 1955","children":[],"tail":", amended section generally to continue agricultural research at the agricultural experiment stations, to restate the declaration of purpose, and to insert definitions of “State” and “State agricultural experiment station.” Former provisions which required division of appropriations between colleges of same state are now contained in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s361h"},"text":"section 361h of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idee2a5076-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idee2a5077-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1974 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/471"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–471","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":", unless "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/471"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–471","children":[],"tail":" repealed by District of Columbia Council after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1975","children":[],"tail":", and prior to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":"; or such amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/471"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–471","children":[],"tail":", as amended by the District Council, also effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":", or some other date prescribed by the Council as authorized under provisions of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/471/s407"},"text":"section 407 of Pub. L. 93–471","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idee2a5078-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1972 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/318"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–318","children":[],"tail":" effective after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1970","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/318/s506/n"},"text":"section 506(n) of Pub. L. 92–318","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s326a"},"text":"section 326a of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"idee2a5079-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1887-03-02/ch314/s10"},"text":"Act Mar. 2, 1887, ch. 314, § 10","children":[],"tail":", as added by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/185/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–185, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-06-23"},"text":"June 23, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/526"},"text":"112 Stat. 526","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/185/s3/b"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 361a to 361i of this title] may be cited as the ‘Hatch Act of 1887’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idee2a507a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Arlington Estate","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Besides the provisions establishing agricultural experiment stations, contained in act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1887-03-02"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1887","children":[],"tail":", a portion of the Arlington estate in the State of Virginia was set apart for experimental agricultural purposes by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1900-04-18/ch243"},"text":"act April 18, 1900, ch. 243","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/135"},"text":"31 Stat. 135","children":[],"tail":", and provisions for establishing and maintaining a general experimental farm and agricultural station thereon were made by the subsequent agricultural appropriation acts."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idee2a507b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idee2a507c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Admission of Alaska and Hawaii to Statehood","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Alaska was admitted into the Union on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1959","children":[],"tail":", on issuance of Proc. No. 3269, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 1959","children":[],"tail":", 24 F.R. 81, 73 Stat. c16, and Hawaii was admitted into the Union on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1959","children":[],"tail":", on issuance of Proc. No. 3309, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1959","children":[],"tail":", 24 F.R. 6868, 73 Stat. c74. For Alaska Statehood Law, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–508","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/339"},"text":"72 Stat. 339","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s21"},"text":"section 21 of Title 48","children":[],"tail":", Territories and Insular Possessions. For Hawaii Statehood Law, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-03-18"},"text":"Mar. 18, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/4"},"text":"73 Stat. 4","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t48/s491"},"text":"section 491 of Title 48","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
